cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for learning unsupervised sentence representations, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The method is based on Generative Latent Optimization, which is a machine learning technique, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper does not impose any assumptions on how words are combined, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. The paper also discusses a Bag of Words model and a variant that models word positions, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well. Finally, the paper reports experimental results and compares its method to other existing methods, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as well.
